<p><strong>When She Talked Back: An Exclusive Q&amp;A with Alesana Marie</strong></p>
<p><strong>Q: Alesana, your novel "When She Talked Back" delves into a thought-provoking exploration of silenced voices. What inspired you to write this story?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> I was inspired by the countless stories I've heard from women and girls who have been silenced or dismissed when they speak up. I wanted to create a character who embodies their resilience and the power of their voices.</p>
<p><strong>Q: The protagonist, Anya, faces significant challenges as a young girl in a conservative society. How did you capture her inner struggles and growth authentically?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> I spent a lot of time researching the experiences of girls and women in similar circumstances. I also drew inspiration from my own experiences as a teenage girl. Anya's journey reflects the internal struggles and determination that many young people face when navigating societal expectations.</p>
<p><strong>Q: The novel tackles themes of gender inequality and the importance of female empowerment. How do you hope readers will engage with these issues?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> I hope readers will be inspired to challenge societal norms and biases that silence women and girls. I want them to reflect on the ways in which they can create a more just and equitable society where all voices are valued.</p>
<p><strong>Q: "When She Talked Back" is a coming-of-age story that explores the complexities of identity and self-discovery. What do you hope readers will take away from Anya's journey?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> I hope readers will understand the importance of embracing their true selves and finding strength in their individuality. Anya's journey shows that it is possible to overcome adversity and find your voice, even in the face of opposition.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Where can readers access a softcopy PDF copy of "When She Talked Back"?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Readers can purchase a softcopy PDF copy of "When She Talked Back" on Amazon Kindle, Barnes &amp; Noble Nook, and other major online retailers.</p>